                     <interp inst="t17990911-74-person671" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a broker, in Broker's-alley; I bought this stand at Mr. Hemens's in Frith-street, on a Tuesday, I believe, the 20th of August.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17990911-74-person672">
                  SARAH
                   WILD
               <interp inst="t17990911-74-person672" type="surname" value="WILD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17990911-74-person672" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17990911-74-person672" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - This was my stand; I sent it to Mr. Barrett's, with some other goods to dispose of.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's defence. I am innocent of the charge; if I had stolen this stand, I should not have put it into a public auction, where there are so many people coming backwards and forwards, and chiefly brokers.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called four witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>
